title: For Sale:  Marlin 1894C .357 / 38 carbine lever action
postcontent:
If you've been looking for an 1894 in .357, then you really don't need me to describe this one.  As described in title, checkered walnut stock, 18" barrel, LNIB.
First off, it is a 2012 model.  Yes, I know older JM stamped Marlins command a premium, but don't believe all the internet griping either by folks repeating old tapes .  There were teething pains early on when Freedom Group bought Marlin, but this was built several years after that.  But Marlin hasn't made 1894's in .357 in a couple of years now, and if you call Marlin they will tell you they don't know when they will again.
The finish, wood-to-metal tolerances, and action are all good and smooth.  No scratches, dings, or anything else.  
I put 9 rounds -- one magazine tube worth -- through the rifle, to test for function, and then it has sat in the safe totally unused.  I could clean it, put a light coat of oil on it, call it BNIB and you wouldn't know.  Have the original plastic wrap and box.
The picture attached is a generic pic off of Google simply because it's a better picture than I could take -- this one is exactly the same.  If you want another view I'll take a pic and email it to you.
It's a fantastic, handy sized carbine.  When I shot the 38's through it, it literally recoiled like a .22.  (I did not try any .357's, but obviously it will handle those as well, as stamped on the barrel).
Not interested in trades.

$___ for shipping costs?

I've put less than 100 rounds through mine, and it's worked perfectly 100% of the time. So it's not new, but it's less than 100 rounds from new, and is fully loaded as you can see... EXCEPT that this listing does NOT come with the flip-up MBUS sights shown in the pictures because I need to keep them for another purpose.

The photo shows this MechTech mounted on a Gen 4 Glock 17 - so please note: the Glock is NOT included in this sale. This listing is for the upper only (no sights). If you have a Glock 17 of any generation, it will fit and function perfectly on this upper, and I think that even a Glock 22 will work on it, as long as you use 9mm mags.

I will meet you in metro Birmingham, or I will ship it to you (where it's legal, which I think is everywhere) if you pay the shipping costs. Compared to a new one, this is a great deal to save over $100.
